Rating: 2
These were fine -- nothing special. The ten-minute prep time was nice, especially for a weeknight, but if you have time, make the Fried Fish Tacos on this site (http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/recipe_views/views/103714) instead. I added guacamole and salsa on top to make these less boring. (And it may be heretical to say so, but I think I prefer plain sour cream to the Rubio's-style sauce in this recipe. Mayonnaise on tacos must be an aquired taste.)

Rating: 3
